World Trade Organisation members have selected two final candidates – Nigeria’s Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala and South Korea’s Yoo Myung-hee – to advance to the final round in the race to lead the Geneva-based trade body, Bloomberg has reported. By advancing two women to the final round of the selection process, the WTO will likely have the first female Director-General in its 25-year history.  Okonjo-Iweala served two stints as Nigeria’s Finance Minister and one term as Foreign Affairs Minister. See Also






